name: Pondok Kopi Penglipuran
address: H9G5+M34, Desa, Penglipuran, Kubu, Kec. Bangli, Kabupaten Bangli, Bali 80613, Indonesia
review 1:
Nestled in a peaceful-er corner of an already super peaceful village. Great space to sit and relax. They have a small selection of beverages (coffee and non-coffee) and snacks. They have some packaged snacks as well.

Tried the Vietnamese drip, it was on the stronger side (for my taste) but it was well made
review 2:
Truly hidden gem inside Penglipuran Village.
Price is really affordable, and beyond expectation because it is located in tourism spot. Taste of the f&b also good.
No heavy food available, only snack and it is enough ü´∂üèº

review 4: Great place, great staff, great coffee! Nice hidden with beautiful garden to rest, drink and snack. Highly recommended!
review 5: Peaceful garden in the backyard, yummie home made, organic coffee and extremly kind, young staffüòä. It was a pleasure to sit under the trees and have some rest.

review 1:
Suki, I can‚Äôt thank you and your family enough for that short yet memorable stay. What an awesome place you have.
Suksuma üôè
review 2: This homestay was the highlight of our trip to Bali. Suki and his family were the perfect hosts. The homestay rooms are very clean, spacious and fitted out well with a lovely porch area and Koi fish pond that has a lovely water feature that relaxes your mind with the sound of flowing water. Priced correctly considering that it is situated in the heart of Penglipuram village, this homestay is a perfect place to enjoy your time away from home but feel right at home with the family. The family and generally the people of the village are truly lovely and beautiful to live with and made us feel welcome and loved over the 5 days and 4 nights that we spent there. A class of its own. We will cherish the experience we had here and will certainly be back for more in the years to come.
review 3: Amazing Homestay with great owners, especially dinner and breakfast. Quiet and near a walkable bamboo forest!
